               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Dāwit “Psalter” (fols. 5r-188r)
 I-1) Mazmura Dāwit “Psalms of
                     David” (fols. 5r-148v)
 I-2) Maḥālǝya nabiyāt “The Canticles of the
                     Prophets” (fols. 148v-163v)
 I-3) Maḥālǝya maḥālǝy “Song of Songs” (fols.
                     163v-172v)
 I-4) Wǝddāse Māryām “Praise of Mary” (fols. 173ra-183rb)
                     I-5) ʾAnqaṣa bǝrhān “The Gate of Light” (fols. 183rb-188rb)
 
                     Additiones 1-3.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="5r" to="188r"/>
                     <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2701Dawit">Psalter</title>
                     
                     <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="5r" to="148v"/>
                        <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</title>
                        
                        
                        <note>- Many Psalms have the words ሃሌ፡ ሉያ፡ መዝሙር፡ ዘዳዊት። instead of the
                           traditional title.</note>
                        <note>- Traditional interpretation of the Hebrew letters in P118 is missing.</note>
                        <note>- Text I-3 has ስብሐት፡ ለአብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ (ለዓለም፡ ወለዓለመ፡ ዓለም።) instead
                           of the traditional titles.</note>
                        <note>- Stichometry (number of lines of each Ps.) is indicated by the word ቃሉ
                           followed by a number, written in red or black.</note>
                        <note>- Final note on stichometry and the midpoint of the Psalter on <locus target="#163v">163v</locus>.</note>
                        <note>- P118 and 151 are not numbered.</note>
                     </msItem>                     
