                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc>- ff. 1-4 are additional leaves originating from another
                           manuscript used as end leaves and containing a Malkǝʾa-Hymn to St
                           Mary.
 - Minor notes: e.g., <locus target="#5r">5r</locus>, 172r,
                           173r.
 - Short supplication for the owners, written in a recent
                           secondary hand on many folios: e.g. 42v, 59r, 83r, 115r, 130r, 148v,
                           172r.
 - The scribe reduced the size of his handwriting to
                           accommodate the end of the line: <locus target="#130v">130v</locus>,
                           131r, 157v. 
 - The scribe used compressed script: <locus target="#119v">119v</locus>, 140v, 157r.
 - Omitted letters,
                           words, lines or passages have been inserted interlineally in small script
                           on many fols.: <locus target="#26v">26v</locus>, 40r, 69r, 81r, 98v,
                           117v. 
 - Corrections written over erasures on many fols.: <locus target="#24v">24v</locus>, 37r, 42v, 85r, 115r, 158v, 186r.
 -
                           Erasures marked with thin lines: <locus target="#37r">37r</locus>, 70v,
                           81r, 134v, 159r.
 - Erasures: <locus target="#50r">50r</locus>, 64r,
                           68r.
 - Scribbles and doodles on many fols.: <locus target="#13v">13v</locus>, 21r, 37v, 61v, 99r, 131v.</desc></item>
                     </list>
